float a = 7/4 * 9/2;
The division operations involve integers, so integer arithmetic will be used, potentially resulting in truncation.

7/4 = 1 (since it's integer division)
9/2 = 4 (again, integer division)

1 * 4 = 4

Thus, the value of a will be 4.0.

-----------------------------------------------------------------

int a = 7*49/7 + 35/7;
7*49 = 343
343/7 = 49

35/7 = 5

49 + 5 = 54

So, the value of a will be 54.

------------------------------------------------------------------------